OL,6,FMs Groves added: "As it continued, the
OL,7,Fcomplainant noticed Ms Jones was
OL,8,Fstanding at the bottom of her steps,
OL,9,Fappearing not to know what to do. A
OL,10,Fmale at her property shouted 'kick
OL,11,Fit', which the complainant presumed
OL,12,Fmeant to kick the XL bully away. The
OL,13,FXL bully then returned to the owner,
OL,14,Fwho did apologise.
OL,16,F"But the complainant said he shouldn't
OL,17,Fhave to live in fear of what would
OL,18,Fhappen due to her dog being dangerous.
OL,19,FHe was shaking like a leaf while going
OL,20,Fback into his home with his dog."
