OL,4,Cattacks neighbour's dog
OL,6,FNo injuries were caused during the
OL,7,Fincident, however Ms Jones was found
OL,8,Fguilty of being in charge of a dog
OL,9,Fwhich was "dangerously out of control".
OL,11,FAndrew Costley, her solicitor, said
OL,12,Fshe had no previous convictions and
OL,13,Fthat Sky was a "family dog".
OL,15,FHe added: "There was a lead and collar
OL,16,Fon Sky but it had snapped and the dog
OL,17,Fgot out. It was over in seconds. The
OL,18,Fcomplainant did pick up Ebony, and Ms
OL,19,FJones' son came out and got Sky very,
OL,20,Fvery, quickly."
